The <b>Slaty Vireo</b> (<i>Vireo brevipennis</i>) is an odd <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vireo" title="Vireo">vireo</a> endemic to shrubby highlands of southern <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a>.
It differs from all other vireos in its predominantly slate gray plumage and long tail. These distinctions once afforded it its own genus, <i>Neochloe</i>. It also has green feather edgings on its wings and tail. Its eyes, belly, and chin are snow white, offsetting the otherwise dark gray plumage.
